        "content": "<p>I have some interpolation <code>itp</code> from which I want to find the neighboring points of the grid. I checked the docs and found in the developer documentation section <code>WeightedIndex</code>, which is probably close to what I'm looking for. However, I don't understand the following behavior:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Julia\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">julia</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">typeof</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">itp</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">Extrapolation</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">ScaledInterpolation</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">BSplineInterpolation</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Array</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">},</span> <span class=\"kt\">BSpline</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Linear</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Throw</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">OnGrid</span><span class=\"p\">}}},</span> <span class=\"kt\">NTuple</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Base</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">OneTo</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Int64</span><span class=\"p\">}}},</span> <span class=\"kt\">BSpline</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Linear</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Throw</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">OnGrid</span><span class=\"p\">}}},</span> <span class=\"kt\">NTuple</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">StepRangeLen</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Base</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">TwicePrecision</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">},</span> <span class=\"kt\">Base</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">TwicePrecision</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">}}}},</span> <span class=\"kt\">BSpline</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Linear</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Throw</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">OnGrid</span><span class=\"p\">}}},</span> <span class=\"kt\">Throw</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Nothing</span><span class=\"p\">}}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">julia</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mf\">1.1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">1.1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">julia</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">itp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">...</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mf\">0.47177811607637216</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">julia</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">wis</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">weightedindexes</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">value_weights</span><span class=\"p\">,),</span> <span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">itpinfo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">itp</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">...</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">WeightedAdjIndex</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">}(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">)),</span> <span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">WeightedAdjIndex</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">}(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">)),</span> <span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">WeightedAdjIndex</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">}(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">)),</span> <span class=\"n\">Interpolations</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"kt\">WeightedAdjIndex</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kt\">Float64</span><span class=\"p\">}(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">0.8999999999999999</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.10000000000000009</span><span class=\"p\">)))</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">julia</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">itp</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">itp</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">itp</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">wis</span><span class=\"o\">...</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"mf\">0.02950452575811892</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><a href=\"https://juliamath.github.io/Interpolations.jl/latest/devdocs/#Interpolation\">According to the docs</a> the evaluation of the <code>itp</code> as well as <code>itp.itp.itp[wis...]</code> should yield the same result, shouldn't it?</p>",
